data.body:
On OS X all command-clicks are mapped to a right button click (which is the usual convention under OS X); see `platform/osx/os_osx.mm`:

```
- (void)mouseDown:(NSEvent *)event {
	if (([event modifierFlags] & NSControlKeyMask)) {
		mouse_down_control = true;
		_mouseDownEvent(event, BUTTON_RIGHT, BUTTON_MASK_RIGHT, true);
	} else {
		mouse_down_control = false;
		_mouseDownEvent(event, BUTTON_LEFT, BUTTON_MASK_LEFT, true);
	}
}
```

This means it's not possible to generate a left button click with a control key (since it's immediately mapped to a right click). Any code relying on such command-left click (e.g. adding points with the current polygon 2d code) cannot be reached under OS X thus.

I'm not sure what a good fix would be. One option might be to introduce a new combination for OS X like ctrl-alt-cmd-left click, that is usually used nowhere in Godot, and that is mapped to the usual control-click.
